race.comment: WILL IT SNOW (8) got a well-deserved victory on the Poly here at the latest effort and will have derived a stack of confidence from that win. Successful hoop Martyn sticks in the irons and again gets the benefit of her 2kg claim. Should be right there when the judge calls a halt. FIRE AND LIGHT (14) is yet to miss a drum in five attempts over this staying trip and will be at peak fitness for this. Has to be included. TAJAWAL (1) returned to form with a solid placing in town last time out and gets some weight off with the 3kg claim. Top-three commodity. DOWN UNDER STUNNAH (10) has a win and a second from her past two efforts and it's hard to knock mares in form. Should be thereabouts. VERMEER (7) rounds out the selections in a race with a bunch of chances.
